@subsection MINLO
@cindex MINLO

The following configuration file shows how to implement the MINLO procedure 
from @mycite{Hamilton2012np}. A few things to note are detailed below.
MINLO can also be applied when reading NTuples, see @ref{NTuple production}.
In this case, the scale and K factor must be defined, see @ref{SCALES} and
@ref{KFACTOR}.

@example
@smallformat
@verbatiminclude Examples/FixedOrder_NLO/MINLO/Sherpa.yaml
@end smallformat
@end example

Things to notice:
@itemize
@item The R parameter of the flavour-based kT clustering algorithm can be changed
using @code{MINLO:DELTA_R}.
@item Setting @code{MINLO: @{SUDAKOV_MODE: 0@}} defines whether to include power
corrections stemming from the finite parts in the integral over branching probabilities.
It defaults to 1.
@item The parameter @code{MINLO:SUDAKOV_PRECISION} defines the precision target for
integration of the Sudakov exponent. It defaults to @code{1e-4}.
@end itemize
